Example 2: Telecom Customer Churn

Dataset ini merupakan kumpulan data yang dikumpulkan secara acak dari basis data sebuah perusahaan telekomunikasi di Iran selama periode 12 bulan. Terdapat total 3150 baris data dalam dataset ini, dimana setiap baris mewakili seorang pelanggan, dan terdapat 14 kolom informasi yang terkait dengan setiap pelanggan.

churn_data <- read.csv(file = "customer_churn.csv", header = TRUE)

Peubah-peubah yang akan digunakan adalah:

  • Subscription Length : Total bulan berlangganan pelanggan

  • Second of Use : Total jumlah detik panggilan yang digunakan

  • Frequency of SMS : Total jumlah SMS yang dikirim

  • Customer Value : Nilai pelanggan yang dihitung

Exploratory Data Analysis

Sebaran dari peubah respon yaitu Customer Value

library(ggplot2)
ggplot(churn_data,aes(x=Customer.Value,y = seq_along(Customer.Value))) + 
geom_point(color = "mediumorchid4") + 
xlab("\n\nCustomer Value") + ylab("Customer\n\n") +
theme(axis.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

Hubungan antara Subscription Length dan peubah respon

ggplot(churn_data, aes(x=Subscription.Length,y=Customer.Value)) + 
geom_point(color="steelblue") + 
ylab("Customer Value\n\n") + xlab("\n\nSubscription Length")+
theme(axis.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

Koefisien korelasi antara Subscription Length dan peubah respon

cor(churn_data$Customer.Value,churn_data$Subscription.Length)
## [1] 0.1095648

Variance Inflation Factor

model <- lm(Customer.Value~Subscription.Length+Seconds.of.Use+Frequency.of.SMS, data=churn_data)
library(car)
vif(model)
## Subscription.Length      Seconds.of.Use    Frequency.of.SMS 
##            1.020009            1.024755            1.014751

Building a Regression Model

model_churn <- lm(Customer.Value~Subscription.Length+Seconds.of.Use+Frequency.of.SMS, data=churn_data)

Checking Model Assumptions

Linearity of Data

plot(model_churn, 1)

Testing the Homoscedasticity Assumption

Scale-Location Plot

plot(model_churn, 3)

Breusch-Pagan Test For Homoscedasticity

library(lmtest)
bptest(model_churn)
## 
##  studentized Breusch-Pagan test
## 
## data:  model_churn
## BP = 233.95, df = 3, p-value < 2.2e-16

Testing the Independence (Autocorrelation) Assumption

Durbin Watson Test for Autocorrelation

durbinWatsonTest(model_churn)
##  lag Autocorrelation D-W Statistic p-value
##    1     -0.09857518      2.197144       0
##  Alternative hypothesis: rho != 0

Normality of Residuals

QQ Plot of Residuals

plot(model_churn, 2)

Perform a Shapiro-Wilk Normality Test

library(MASS)
sresid <- studres(model_churn) 
shapiro.test(sresid)
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  sresid
## W = 0.72052, p-value < 2.2e-16
